      "reason": "Python Flask f-string return -> HtmlOutput sink coverage gap. vuln-v1 M2/M3 introduced the HtmlOutput TaintSinkType variant + AST sink entries but did not cover the f-string-return-from-view-function shape (e.g. `@app.route('/x') def view(): return f'<h1>{user_input}</h1>'`). Per `tldr taint` analysis the user-input source IS detected and tracked; only the sink side is missing. Sibling milestone: vuln-source-parity-v1 (1 lang scope expansion to Python — operator review at M5 to confirm the milestone absorbs this entry vs. spawning a tiny dedicated patch milestone)."
